HIGH YIELDING HOTEL - SECURELY LEASED FREEHOLD INVESTMENT

CBRE Hotels are pleased to offer this high yielding pub opportunity providing the following investment highlights:

- Significant investment growth, current rental at $78,000 p.a.*
- Long-term lease with CPI increases, 30 years including options
- Securely leased to experienced hospitality operators
- Generous sized allotment of 1,158 sqm*
- Popular tourism and leisure destination on the Murray River

* approx.

For Sale by Expressions of Interest, closing Thursday 24th June 2021 (if not sold prior).

This property is located on the corner of Queens Road and Harris Road, Five Dock.

A number of individual office suites ranging from 23sqm* - 106sqm* (approx).

All suites have internal kitchenette and car spaces allocated, included in the rental.

The building is well serviced with gym, cafe, car wash and childcare facilities.

Location:
Five Dock is a suburb in the inner-west of Sydney. The subject property is located 10 kilometres west of the Sydney Central Business District, 10 kilometres from the Parramatta CBD and 2.5 kilometres east of the entrance to the M4 Motorway, in the Local Government Area of the City of Canada Bay.

Five Dock lies between Parramatta Road and the City West Link to the south and Hen and Chicken Bay, on the Parramatta River, along with the suburbs of Wareemba and Russell Lea, to the north.

Five Dock is an increasingly popular suburb offering spectacular views to the city to which it is linked by both roads and ferry.

The subject building is located on the high profile corner of Queens Road and Harris Road, directly opposite Rosebank College High School. This is an extremely busy intersection as Queens Road is an important alternate route to Parramatta Road for both east and west bound traffic. There is undercover parking within the building with access off Harris Road and with Five Dock's close proximity to the CBD the site is serviced by public buses, with a stop directly in front of the building.

Contact the exclusive agent today for more information.

*approx*

99 Mount Street provides a rare opportunity for an ambitious hospitality group to make its mark in the heart of North Sydney. A combination of two artfully conceived spaces, with expansive indoor and outdoor seating areas, is the largest of its kind in the area. Positioned on an elevated podium, and commanding views over the  North Sydney cityscape, 99 Mount Street promises to be an unsurpassed gathering place.

Areas

- Internal: 207sqm* - 287sqm* 
- External: 171sqm* - 192sqm*
- Amenities: 33.7sqm*
- Bin Room: 15.4sqm*
- Storeroom: 21 sqm*

Services & Inclusions

- 4.5m* high ceilings 
- Grease, exhaust, gas, water & power to a point
- Air conditioning to a point
- Glass bi-fold doors leading out to the exclusive use external seating areas (totalling up to 192sqm)
- DA approved signage opportunities on both Walker Street and Mount Street
- PSA Liquor Licence for 282 pax in place

Location

- North facing with Direct street access
- Located above national and international retailers including ALDI, JB Hi-Fi, Commonwealth Bank, Boost Juice and directly opposite Coles Supermarket, Betty’s Burgers and Glorietta’s
- 5 minute walk to North Sydney Train & Bus Station and the upcoming Victoria Cross Metro Station and a 3 minute walk to Greenwood Plaza
- Surrounded by soaring office towers including 100 Mount St (34 levels), 118 Mount Street (25 levels) and the brand new home of Channel 9, Microsoft, Luxottica plus many more - 1 Denison (37 levels)
- Minutes to the continually growing residential populations of North Sydney, McMahons Point and Milsons Point
 
With top quality F&B operators such as Barlume (by the Grounds of Alexandria), The Treehouse, Glorietta’s, Greenwood Hotel, The Green Moustache and The Greens, North Sydney has officially cemented itself as a thriving CBD with top class food & beverage operators. 

For further details or to obtain our retail brochure, please contact Amy Pfeiffer 0401 198 401, amy.pfeiffer@cbre.com.au.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Conveniently located in the heart of the tightly held Minjungbal Drive Retail Strip with easy access from the Pacific Motorway, Tweed Hub brings together a diverse mix of retailers such as The Good Guys, First Choice Liquor, Movement Health & Fitness, KFC, Hungry Jacks, the Tweed Banora Medical Centre amongst others.

Tweed Hub has a GLA of 9,652sqm and 240 on grade car parks (2.4 bays per 100sqm), making it one of the only true centres that can cater for a variety of different type of retail uses. Furthermore, the Centre benefits from outstanding exposure onto to Minjungbal Drive which is the major feeder road between the Pacific Motorway and Coolangatta.

The centre is easily accessed from the Pacific Motorway and Coolangatta given that it’s located on the signalised Minjungbal Drive and Shallow Bay Drive intersection, which allows for multidirectional access off Minjungbal Drive.

The Tweed City Sub Regional Shopping Centre is located within 500m from Tweed Hub and is home to major national retailers such as; Coles; Woolworths; Hoyts Cinema; JB Hi Fi; Harris Scarfe; Kmart; Big W; Best & Less and over 140 speciality stores.

On offer are two showroom tenancies available, 280sqm and 103sqm food & beverage earmarked tenancy located on the southern corner of the centre along Minjungbal Drive. These tenancies offer excellent signage and branding opportunities and can be made available.
